{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/diagnosis/assessment/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"8c893fa3-9e5e-5db1-87f3-370e7e9afd70","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 7886082d-29cb-4e68-9bca-a967008d457f --><h2>How should I assess a person with suspected meticillin resistant Staphylococcal aureus (MRSA)?</h2><!-- end field 7886082d-29cb-4e68-9bca-a967008d457f -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 5d493985-19bd-4946-afd2-a967008d454a --><!-- begin field 80912ef7-ca01-4b24-95df-a967008d457f --><ul><li><strong>Take a history asking about:</strong><ul><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/diagnosis/when-to-suspect-mrsa/\">Clinical features</a> — onset and evolution of symptoms.</li><li>Previous treatment including antibiotic use.</li><li>Past medical history including recurrent skin infections.</li><li><a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/background-information/causes/\">Risk factors</a> for MRSA such as recent hospitalization, previous MRSA infection or carriage, indwelling devices (for example urinary catheters) and previous antibiotic use.</li><li>Contacts with similar symptoms, recurrent skin infections or known MRSA infection or carriage.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Examine the person, checking: </strong><ul><li>Vital signs such as temperature, blood pressure, heart rate, capillary refill and oxygen saturations – look for signs of serious illness such as sepsis.</li><li>The relevant systems for <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/diagnosis/when-to-suspect-mrsa/\">clinical signs</a> of Staphylococcal infection (for example discharging skin lesions or lower respiratory tract infection) and <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/background-information/complications/\">complications</a>.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Consider investigations:</strong><ul><li>If the person is well and does not require <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/management/management/#management-in-primary-care\">admission</a> take a sample from the affected area for microscopy and culture, for example, swabs of exudate from lesions or wounds or urine or sputum samples.</li><li>Other investigations such as chest X-ray may be appropriate depending on the specific clinical situation.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 80912ef7-ca01-4b24-95df-a967008d457f --><!-- end item 5d493985-19bd-4946-afd2-a967008d454a -->","topic":{"id":"26f48611-f890-5112-aa26-bef13e5623e1","topicId":"c9e197be-4f79-4d67-bf67-2b2a8a137e03","topicName":"MRSA in primary care","slug":"mrsa-in-primary-care","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2018","chapters":[{"id":"ba15ac05-528a-5474-8925-89cfea95b961","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"97d099f9-1263-51e7-8c71-fb82256182d3","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f6df2380-e42f-563b-8f75-a588376e1da7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"530a7f74-53c2-5e4e-8c1d-ceb01bccf776","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"a17267d5-eb08-5126-9312-b78fee4494a2","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"9537a389-c41a-5355-ac9c-9c56bba48a35","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"124fbaa7-2678-5958-b4be-d5f9be74c18a","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a1ce510-f22c-5132-a344-31bd40831eac","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"8e5d44fe-1deb-51e2-bb59-04ccc35710c7","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"4b396bfd-befc-5055-a086-61c9628b6042","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"db6fe095-36c1-5949-87a9-e1c049f58234","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"e5c4d5c6-ed37-5a97-a1ef-874a072dd190","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"ab09ceb7-2cc4-57c7-a6ec-887e4df64336","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"25bf5688-a664-56d4-b6cd-077f06dc4be5","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"d85a2164-704c-52e3-b5f8-2170aa56ead6","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"06951cf4-8eb9-5dc4-89be-8f9d5c691a2c","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"e6f67db6-38d0-57cd-a3fa-15d68e43e3a3","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"26204955-9976-5215-8ba5-fb73d7b50a95","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"41a2bada-cc7d-5a86-9495-82d662957b3a","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"d4b618cd-66fe-50a0-a686-99007ef42fc3","slug":"when-to-suspect-mrsa","fullItemName":"When to suspect MRSA"},{"id":"8c893fa3-9e5e-5db1-87f3-370e7e9afd70","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"01c6eee3-9b6f-5c05-8f49-c30279e03ddf","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"4d78ace1-1174-5c0f-b2e6-c74c8a51847a","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"ddb73bdb-86dd-524d-92b2-f92b0ca957a0","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"a6c4d845-e78e-5116-b950-e78374132545","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9eb97cdf-d2a2-5018-9667-43dbca0cb266","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"ef38f185-0695-523f-bf60-bd75e123a75e","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"aea98085-ac9a-5b4c-a54b-a8857e1055e1","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"795e0448-4ce8-5b2a-8a85-3aa1ecac9c40","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"834f64f0-6780-5945-914d-8f8a0d4e8dfe","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"7c573460-655d-5212-8d3c-fb5758d25c43","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"43afc1fb-06c4-5ec8-9051-d49b5156cfc6","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"41a2bada-cc7d-5a86-9495-82d662957b3a","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"07e16582-d76a-5a05-9245-4b9bd9bc54ed","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-9fc","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d05a9dd7-c0f9-4ce2-92f7-a97c00e0d8cb --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field d05a9dd7-c0f9-4ce2-92f7-a97c00e0d8cb -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 9fcfd8ed-7025-47e0-88e9-a97c00e0d84d --><!-- begin field 93160513-500f-4f7a-acb4-a97c00e0d8cb --><p>The recommendations on the assessment of a person with suspected meticillin resistant <em>Staphylococcal aureus</em> (MRSA) infection are based on the clinical guidelines <em>Guidelines for UK practice for the diagnosis and management of methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) infections presenting in the community </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Nathwani et al, 2008</a>], Rook’s Textbook of Dermatology [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Hay, 2016</a>] and expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Taylor, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>].</p><ul><li>Consensus opinion in clinical guidelines [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Nathwani et al, 2008</a>], Rook’s textbook of Dermatology [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Hay, 2016</a>] and review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Taylor, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>] is that diagnosis is based on a thorough clinical assessment (including identification of <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/background-information/causes/\">risk factors</a> for MRSA) supported by confirmatory laboratory results to confirm MRSA infection, identify antimicrobial susceptibility and appropriate treatment.</li><li>Evidence from a systematic review to determine whether antibiotic exposure is a risk factor for the isolation of MRSA, showed that people who have taken antibiotics have an almost two-fold chance of acquiring MRSA (either infection or colonization) compared with people who have not taken antibiotics (risk ratio [RR] 1.8, 95% CI 1.7 to 1.9, p < 0.001). The risk is almost three times greater for people who have taken quinolones (RR 2.9, 95% CI 2.5 to 3.5) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/mrsa-in-primary-care/references/\">Tacconelli et al, 2008</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 93160513-500f-4f7a-acb4-a97c00e0d8cb --><!-- end item 9fcfd8ed-7025-47e0-88e9-a97c00e0d84d -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}